content:
To make the background appear infinite on the bottom, you can use a background image that has a repeating pattern. Here's an example:

1. Create a background image with a repeating pattern. You can use an image editor like Photoshop or GIMP to create the pattern. Save the image as a PNG, GIF or JPG.
2. Add the background image to the CSS of your HTML document using the `background-image` property. Set the `background-repeat` property to `repeat` so that the image is repeated both horizontally and vertically.
3. Set the height of the body to `100%` so that it covers the entire height of the viewport.

Here's an example code snippet:
```css
body {
  background-image: url("pattern.png");
  background-repeat: repeat;
  height: 100%;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}
```
In this example, the `background-image` property points to the image file `pattern.png`, which has a repeating pattern. The `background-repeat` property is set to `repeat` to repeat the image both horizontally and vertically. Finally, the `height` property is set to `100%` to cover the entire height of the viewport.
